quran[431]{c,v,t}:
  67,1,"Blessed be He in whose hand is the kingdom, for He is mighty over all"
  67,2,"Who created death and life, to try you, which of you does best; for He is the mighty, the forgiving"
  67,3,Who created seven heavens in stories; thou canst not see any discordance in the creation of the Merciful
  67,4,"Why, look again! canst thou see a flaw? Then look again twice!- thy look shall return to thee driven back and dulled"
  67,5,And we have adorned the lower heaven with lamps; and set them to pelt the devils with; and we have prepared for them the torment of the blaze
  67,6,"And for those who disbelieve in their Lord is the torment of hell, and an evil journey shall it be"
  67,7,When they shall be cast therein they shall hear its braying as it boils
  67,8,"it will well-nigh burst for rage! Whenever a troop of them is thrown in, its treasurers shall ask them, 'Did not a warner come to you"
  67,9,"They shall say, 'Yea! a warner came to us, and we called him liar, and said, \"God has not sent down aught; ye are but in great error"
  67,10,"And they shall say, 'Had we but listened or had sense we had not been amongst the fellows of the blaze"
  67,11,And they will confess their sins; but 'Avaunt to the fellows of the blaze
  67,12,"Verily, those who fear their Lord in secret, for them is forgiveness and a great hire"
  67,13,"Speak ye secretly or openly, verily, He knows the nature of men's breasts"
  67,14,"Ay! He knows who created! for He is the subtle, the well-aware"
  67,15,He it is who made the earth flat for you; so walk in the spacious sides thereof and eat of His provision; for unto Him the resurrection is
  67,16,"Are ye sure that He who is in the heaven will not cleave the earth with you, and that it then shall quake"
  67,17,"Or are ye sure that He who is in the heaven will not send against you a heavy sand storm, and that ye then shall know how the warning was"
  67,18,"But those before them did call the apostles liars, and what a change it was"
  67,19,Or have they not looked at the birds above them expanding their wings or closing them? - none holds them in except the Merciful One; for He on everything doth look
  67,20,"Or who is this who will be a host for you, to help you against the Merciful?- the misbelievers are only in delusion"
  67,21,"Or who is this who will provide you if He hold back His provision? - Nay, but they persist in perverseness and aversion"
  67,22,Is he who walks prone upon his face more guided than he who walks upright upon a straight path
  67,23,"Say, 'It is He who produced you and made for you hearing and sight and hearts' - little is it that ye give thanks"
  67,24,"Say, 'It is He who sowed you in the earth, and unto Him shall ye be gathered"
  67,25,"They say, 'When shall this threat be, if ye do speak the truth"
  67,26,"Say, 'The knowledge is only with God; and I am but a plain warner"
  67,27,"And when they see it nigh, sorry shall be the faces of those who misbelieve; and it shall be said, 'This is that for which ye used to call"
  67,28,"Say, 'Have ye considered, whether God destroy me and those with me, or whether we obtain mercy, yet who will protect the misbelievers from grievous torment"
  67,29,"Say, 'He is the Merciful; we believe in Him, and upon Him do we rely; and ye shall shortly know who it is that is in obvious error"
  67,30,"Say, 'Have ye considered if your waters on the morrow should have sunk, who is to bring you flowing water"
  68,1,"By the pen, and what they write"
  68,2,"thou art not, by God's grace, mad"
  68,3,"and, verily, thine is a hire that is not grudged"
  68,4,"and, verily, thou art of a grand nature"
  68,5,But thou shalt see and they shall see
  68,6,which of you is the infatuated
  68,7,"Verily, thy Lord He knows best who errs from His way; and He knows best those who are guided"
  68,8,Then obey not those who call thee liar
  68,9,"they would fain that thou shouldst be smooth with them, then would they be smooth with thee"
  68,10,And obey not any mean swearer
  68,11,"a back-biter, a walker about with slander"
  68,12,"a forbidder of good, a transgressor, a sinner"
  68,13,"rude, and base-born too"
  68,14,though he have wealth and sons
  68,15,"When our signs are recited to him he says, 'Old folks' tales"
  68,16,We will brand him on the snout
  68,17,"Verily, we have tried them as we tried the fellows of the garden when they swore, 'We will cut its fruit at morn"
  68,18,But they made not the exception
  68,19,and there came round about it an encompassing calamity from thy Lord the while they slept
  68,20,and on the morrow it was as one the fruit of which is cut
  68,21,And they cried to each other in the morning
  68,22,Go early to your tilth if ye would cut it
  68,23,"So they set off, saying privily to each other"
  68,24,There shall surely enter it today unto you no poor person
  68,25,And they went early deciding to be stingy
  68,26,"And when they saw it they said, 'Verily, we have erred"
  68,27,"Nay, we are forbidden (its fruit)"
  68,28,"Said the most moderate of them, 'Said I not to you, \"unless ye celebrate God's praises"
  68,29,"Said they, 'Celebrated be the praises of our Lord! verily, we were unjust"
  68,30,And they approached each other with mutual blame
  68,31,"Said they, 'O woe to us! verily, we have been outrageous"
  68,32,"Haply our Lord may give us instead a better than it; verily, we unto our Lord do yearn"
  68,33,"Thus is the torment, but, verily, the torment of the hereafter is greater, if ye did but know"
  68,34,"Verily, for the pious with their Lord are gardens of pleasure"
  68,35,Shall we then make the Muslims like the sinners
  68,36,What ails you? how ye judge
  68,37,Or have ye a book in which ye can study
  68,38,that ye are surely to have what ye may choose
  68,39,Or have ye oaths binding on us until the judgment day that ye are surely to have what ye may judge
  68,40,"Ask them, which of them will vouch for this"
  68,41,"Or have they partners, then let them bring their partners if they do speak the truth"
  68,42,On the day when the leg shall be bared; and they shall be called to adore and shall not be able
  68,43,"Lowering their looks, abasement shall attack them, for they were called to adore while yet they were safe"
  68,44,But let me alone with him who calls this new discourse a lie. We will surely bring them down by degrees from whence they do not know
  68,45,And I will let them have their way! for my device is sure
  68,46,Or dost thou ask them a hire for it while they are burdened with debts
  68,47,"Or have they the knowledge of the unseen, so that they write"
  68,48,"But wait patiently for the judgment of thy Lord, and be not like the fellow of the fish, when he cried out as he was choking with rage"
  68,49,"Had it not been that grace from his Lord reached him, he would have been cast out on the naked (shore) and blamed the while"
  68,50,"But his Lord elected him, and made him of the pious"
  68,51,"The misbelievers well-nigh upset thee with their looks when they hear the reminder, and they say, 'Surely he is mad"
  68,52,And yet it is but a reminder to the worlds
  69,1,The Infallible
  69,2,what is the Infallible
  69,3,and what should make thee know what the Infallible is
  69,4,Thamud and 'Ad called the Striking Day a lie
  69,5,but as for Thamud they perished by the shock
  69,6,and as for 'Ad they perished with the violent cold blast of wind
  69,7,which He subjected against them for seven nights and eight days consecutively
  69,8,"Thou mightest see the people therein prostrate as though they were palm stumps thrown down, and canst thou see any of them left"
  69,9,And Pharaoh and those before him of the overturned Cities committed sins
  69,10,"and they rebelled against the apostle of their Lord, and He seized them with an excessive punishment"
  69,11,"Verily, we, when the water surged, bore you on it in a sailing ship"
  69,12,"to make it a memorial for you, and that the retentive ear might hold it"
  69,13,And when the trumpet shall be blown with one blast
  69,14,"and the earth shall be borne away, and the mountains too, and both be crushed with one crushing"
  69,15,on that day shall the inevitable happen
  69,16,"and the heaven on that day shall be cleft asunder, for on that day shall it wane"
  69,17,and the angels upon the sides thereof; and above them on that day shall eight bear the throne of thy Lord
  69,18,On the day when ye shall be set forth no hidden thing of yours shall be concealed
  69,19,"And as for him who is given his book in his right hand, he shall say, 'Here! take and read my book"
  69,20,"Verily, I thought that I should meet my reckoning"
  69,21,and he shall be in a pleasing life
  69,22,in a lofty garden
  69,23,whose fruits are nigh to cull
  69,24,"Eat ye and drink with good digestion, for what ye did aforetime in the days that have gone by"
  69,25,"But as for him who is given his book in his left hand he shall say, 'O, would that I had not received my book"
  69,26,I did not know what my account would be
  69,27,"O, would that it had been an end of me"
  69,28,my wealth availed me not
  69,29,my authority has perished from me
  69,30,Take him and fetter him
  69,31,then in hell broil him
  69,32,then into a chain whose length is seventy cubits force him
  69,33,"verily, he believed not in the mighty God"
  69,34,nor was he particular to feed the poor
  69,35,therefore he has not here today any warm friend
  69,36,nor any food except foul ichor
  69,37,which none save sinners shall eat
  69,38,I need not swear by what ye see
  69,39,or what ye do not see
  69,40,"verily, it is the speech of a noble apostle"
  69,41,"and it is not the speech of a poet:- little is it ye believe"
  69,42,"And it is not the speech of a soothsayer,- little is it that ye mind"
  69,43,a revelation from the Lord of the worlds
  69,44,Why if he had invented against us any sayings
  69,45,we would have seized him by the right hand
  69,46,then we would have cut his jugular vein
  69,47,nor could any one of you have kept us off from him
  69,48,"Verily, it is a memorial to the pious"
  69,49,"and, verily, we know that there are amongst you those who say it is a lie"
  69,50,"and, verily, it is a source of sighing to the misbelievers"
  69,51,"and, verily, it is certain truth"
  69,52,Therefore celebrate the name of thy mighty Lord
  70,1,An asker asked for torment that must befall
  70,2,for the unbelievers; there is no repelling it
  70,3,from God the Lord of the ascents
  70,4,whereby ascend the angels and the Spirit unto Him in a day whose length is fifty thousand years
  70,5,Wherefore be patient with fair patience
  70,6,"verily, they see it as afar off"
  70,7,but we see it nigh
  70,8,The day when the heaven shall be as molten brass
  70,9,and the mountains shall be like flocks of wool
  70,10,when no warm friend shall question friend
  70,11,"they shall gaze on each other, and the sinner would fain give as a ransom from the torment of that day his sons"
  70,12,"and his mate, and his brother"
  70,13,and his kin who stand by him
  70,14,"and all who are in the earth, that yet it might rescue him"
  70,15,"Nay, verily, it is a flame"
  70,16,dragging by the scalp
  70,17,it shall call those who retreated and turned their backs
  70,18,and who amassed and hoarded
  70,19,"Verily, man is by nature rash"
  70,20,"when evil touches him, very impatient"
  70,21,"when good touches him, niggardly"
  70,22,all save those who pray
  70,23,who remain at their prayers
  70,24,and in whose wealth is a reasonable due (set aside)
  70,25,for him who asks and him who is kept from asking
  70,26,and those who believe in a day of judgment
  70,27,and those who shrink in terror from the torment of their Lord
  70,28,"verily, the torment of their Lord is not safe"
  70,29,and those who guard their private parts
  70,30,"except for their wives or the (slave girls) whom their right hands possess, for they are not to be blamed"
  70,31,"but whoso craves beyond this, they are the transgressors"
  70,32,and those who observe their trusts and their compacts
  70,33,and those who are upright in their testimonies
  70,34,and those who keep their prayers
  70,35,these shall dwell in gardens honoured
  70,36,What ails the misbelievers that they hurry on before thee
  70,37,crowding together on the right and on the left
  70,38,Does every man of them wish to enter the garden of pleasure
  70,39,"Nay, we created them of what they know"
  70,40,"And I need not swear by the Lord of the easts and the wests; verily, we are able"
  70,41,"to change them for others better, nor are we prevented"
  70,42,"So leave them to plunge in discussion, and to play until they meet that day of theirs which they are threatened with"
  70,43,"the day when they shall come forth in haste from the graves, as though they flock to a standard"
  70,44,with their looks abashed; meanness shall cover them! That is the day which they were promised
  71,1,"Verily, we sent Noah to his people, 'Warn thy people before there come to them a grievous torment"
  71,2,"Said he, 'O my people! verily, I am to you an obvious warner"
  71,3,that ye serve God and fear Him and obey me
  71,4,"He will pardon you your sins, and will defer you unto an appointed time; verily, God's appointed time when it comes will not be deferred, did ye but know"
  71,5,"Said he, 'My Lord! verily, I have called my people by night and day"
  71,6,and my call did but increase them in flight
  71,7,"and, verily, every time I called them, that Thou mightest pardon them, they placed their fingers in their ears and tried to cover themselves with their garments and persisted, and were very big with pride"
  71,8,Then I called them openly
  71,9,then I published to them and I spoke to them in secret
  71,10,"and I said, \"Ask forgiveness of your Lord, verily, He is very forgiving"
  71,11,He will send the rain upon you in torrents
  71,12,"and will extend to you wealth and children, and will make for you gardens, and will make for you rivers"
  71,13,What ails you that ye hope not for something serious from God
  71,14,when He has created you by steps
  71,15,Do ye not see how God has created the seven heavens in stories
  71,16,"and has set the moon therein for a light, and set the sun for a lamp"
  71,17,and God has made you grow out of the earth
  71,18,"and then He will make you return thereto, and will make you come forth therefrom"
  71,19,and God has made for you the earth a carpet
  71,20,that ye may walk therein in broad paths
  71,21,"Said Noah, 'My Lord! verily, they have rebelled against me, and followed him whose wealth and children have but added to his loss"
  71,22,and they have plotted a great plot
  71,23,"and said, \"Ye shall surely not leave your gods: ye shall surely neither leave Wadd, nor Suwah, nor Yaghuth, nor Ya'uq, nor Nasr"
  71,24,"and they led astray many.\"' And thou (Mohammed) wilt only increase the unjust in their error"
  71,25,"because of their sins they were drowned and made to enter into the fire, and they found no helpers against God"
  71,26,"And Noah said, 'My Lord! leave not upon the earth one dweller of the misbelievers"
  71,27,"Verily, Thou, if Thou shouldst leave them, they will lead astray Thy servants, and they will only bear for children sinners and misbelievers"
  71,28,"My Lord! pardon me and my two parents, and whomsoever enters my house believing, and (pardon) the believers men and women - but Thou shalt only increase the unjust in loss"
  72,1,"Say, 'I have been inspired that there listened a company of the ginn, and they said, \"We have heard a marvellous Qur'an"
  72,2,"that guides to the right direction; and we believe therein, and we join no one with our Lord"
  72,3,"for, verily, He - may the majesty of our Lord be exalted!- has taken to Himself neither consort nor son"
  72,4,"And, verily, a fool among us spake against God wide of the mark"
  72,5,And we thought that men and ginn would never speak a lie against God
  72,6,And there are persons amongst men who seek for refuge with persons amongst the ginn; but they increase them in their perverseness
  72,7,"And they thought, as ye thought, that God would not raise up any one from the dead"
  72,8,But we touched the heavens and found them filled with a mighty guard and shooting-stars
  72,9,and we did sit in certain seats thereof to listen; but whoso of us listens now finds a shooting-star for him on guard
  72,10,"And, verily, we know not whether evil be meant for those who are in the earth, or if their Lord means right by them"
  72,11,"And of us are some who are pious, and of us are some who are otherwise: we are in separate bands"
  72,12,"And we thought that we could not frustrate God in the earth, and could not frustrate Him by flight"
  72,13,"But, verily, when we heard the guidance we believed therein, and he who believes in his Lord shall fear neither diminution nor loss"
  72,14,"And, verily, of us are some who are Muslims, and of us some are trespassers; but those of us who are Muslims they strive after right direction"
  72,15,and as for the trespassers they are fuel for hell
  72,16,"And if they will go right upon the way, we will irrigate them with copious water"
  72,17,to try them thereby; and whoso turns from the remembrance of his Lord He will drive him to severe torment
  72,18,"And (say) that the mosques are God's, and that ye should not call on any one with God"
  72,19,and that when God's servant stood up to pray they called out to him and well-nigh crowded upon him
  72,20,"Say, 'I only call upon my Lord, and I join no one with Him"
  72,21,"Say, 'Verily, I cannot control for you either harm, or right direction"
  72,22,"Say, 'Verily, as for me none can protect me against God, nor do I find any refuge beside Him"
  72,23,"except delivering the message from God and His errands: and whoso rebels against God and His Apostle, verily, for him is the fire of hell for them to dwell therein for ever and for aye"
  72,24,"Until when they see what they are threatened with, then shall they surely know who is most weak at helping and fewest in numbers"
  72,25,"Say, 'I know not if what ye are threatened with be nigh, or if my Lord will set for it a term"
  72,26,"He knows the unseen, and He lets no one know His unseen"
  72,27,"save such apostle as He is well pleased with: for, verily, He sends marching before him and behind him a guard"
  72,28,"That He may know that they have delivered the errands of their Lord, for He compasses what they have, and reckons everything by number"
  73,1,O thou who art enwrapped
  73,2,rise by night except a little
  73,3,the half or deduct therefrom a little
  73,4,"or add thereto, and chant the Qur'an chanting"
  73,5,"Verily, we will cast on thee a heavy speech"
  73,6,"Verily, the early part of the night is stronger in impressions and more upright in speech"
  73,7,"Verily, thou hast by day a long employment"
  73,8,but mention the name of thy Lord and devote thyself thoroughly to Him
  73,9,the Lord of the east and the west; there is no god but He; then take Him for a guardian
  73,10,"And endure patiently what they say, and flee from them with a decorous flight"
  73,11,"And leave me and those who say it is a lie, who are possessed of comfort; and let them bide for a while"
  73,12,"Verily, with us are heavy fetters and hell-fire"
  73,13,"and food that chokes, and mighty woe"
  73,14,On the day when the earth and the mountains shall tremble and the earth shall be as a crumbling sand-hill
  73,15,"Verily, we have sent unto you an apostle bearing witness against you, as we sent an apostle unto Pharaoh"
  73,16,"But Pharaoh rebelled against the apostle, and we seized him with an overpowering punishment"
  73,17,Then how will ye shield yourselves if ye misbelieve from the day which shall make children grey-headed
  73,18,whereon the heaven cleaves - its promise shall be fulfilled
  73,19,"Verily, this is a memorial, and whoso will, let him take unto his Lord a way"
  73,20,"Verily, thy Lord knows that thou dost stand up to pray nearly two-thirds of the night, or the half of it or the third of it, as do part of those who are with thee; for God measures the night and the day; He knows that ye cannot calculate it, and He turns relentant towards you. So read what is easy of the Qur'an. He knows that there will be of you some who are sick and others who beat about in the earth craving the grace of God, and others who are fighting in the cause of God. Then read what is easy of it and be steadfast in prayer, and give alms, and lend to God a goodly loan, for what ye send forward for yourselves of good ye will find it with God. It is better and a greater hire; and ask ye pardon of God: verily, God is forgiving, merciful"
  74,1,O thou who art covered
  74,2,rise up and warn
  74,3,And thy Lord magnify
  74,4,And thy garments purify
  74,5,And abomination shun
  74,6,And grant not favours to gain increase
  74,7,And for thy Lord await
  74,8,And when the trump is blown
  74,9,for that day is a difficult day
  74,10,for the misbelievers aught but easy
  74,11,Leave me alone with him I have created
  74,12,and for whom I have made extensive wealth
  74,13,and sons that he may look upon
  74,14,and for whom I have smoothed things down
  74,15,Then he desires that I should increase
  74,16,"nay, verily, he is hostile to our signs"
  74,17,I will drive him up a hill
  74,18,Then he reflected and planned
  74,19,"May he be killed, - how he planned"
  74,20,"Again, may he be killed, - how he planned"
  74,21,Then he looked
  74,22,then he frowned and scowled
  74,23,then he retreated and was big with pride
  74,24,"and said, 'This is only magic exhibited"
  74,25,this is only mortal speech
  74,26,I will broil him in hell-fire
  74,27,and what shall make thee know what hell-fire is
  74,28,It will not leave and will not let alone
  74,29,It scorches the flesh
  74,30,over it are nineteen (angels)
  74,31,"We have made only angels guardians of the fire, and we have only made their number a trial to those who misbelieve; that those who have been given the Book may be certain, and that those who believe may be increased in faith; and that those who have been given the Book and the believers may not doubt; and that those in whose hearts is sickness, and the misbelievers may say, 'What does God mean by this as a parable?' Thus God leads astray whom He pleases, and guides him He pleases: and none knows the hosts of thy Lord save Himself; and it is only a reminder to mortals"
  74,32,"Nay, by the moon"
  74,33,And the night when it retires
  74,34,And the morning when it brightly dawns
  74,35,"Verily, it is one of the greatest misfortunes"
  74,36,a warning to mortals
  74,37,for him amongst you who wishes to press forward or to tarry
  74,38,Every soul is pledged for what it earns
  74,39,except the fellows of the right
  74,40,in gardens shall they ask each other
  74,41,about the sinners
  74,42,What drove you into hell-fire
  74,43,"They shall say, 'We weren't of those who prayed"
  74,44,we didn't feed the poor
  74,45,but we did plunge into discussion with those who plunged
  74,46,and we called the judgment day a lie
  74,47,until the certainty did come to us
  74,48,But there shall not profit them the intercession of the intercessors
  74,49,What ailed them that they turned away from the memorial
  74,50,as though they were timid asses
  74,51,fleeing from a lion
  74,52,"Nay, every man of them wished that he might have given him books spread open"
  74,53,"Nay, but they did not fear the hereafter"
  74,54,"Nay, it is a memorial"
  74,55,and let him who will remember it
  74,56,but none will remember it except God please. He is most worthy of fear; and he is most worthy to forgive
  75,1,I need not swear by the resurrection day
  75,2,Nor need I swear by the self-accusing soul
  75,3,Does man think that we shall not collect his bones
  75,4,Able are we to arrange his finger tips
  75,5,"Nay, but man wishes to be wicked henceforward"
  75,6,"he asks, When is the resurrection day"
  75,7,But when the sight shall be dazed
  75,8,and the moon be eclipsed
  75,9,and the sun and the moon be together
  75,10,"and man shall say upon that day, 'Where is a place to flee to"
  75,11,"nay, no refuge"
  75,12,and to thy Lord that day is the sure settlement
  75,13,He will inform man on that day of what He has sent forward or delayed
  75,14,"Nay, man is an evidence against himself"
  75,15,and even if he thrusts forward his excuses
  75,16,Do not move thy tongue thereby to hasten it
  75,17,It is for us to collect it and to read it
  75,18,and when we read it then follow its reading
  75,19,And again it is for us to explain it
  75,20,"Nay, indeed, but ye love the transient life"
  75,21,and ye neglect the hereafter
  75,22,Faces on that day shall be bright
  75,23,gazing on their Lord
  75,24,And faces on that day shall be dismal
  75,25,Thou wilt think that a back-breaking calamity has happened to them
  75,26,"Nay, but when the [soul] comes up into the throat"
  75,27,"and it is said, 'Who will charm it back"
  75,28,"and he will think that it is his parting [hour]"
  75,29,And leg shall be pressed on leg
  75,30,unto thy Lord on that day shall the driving be
  75,31,For he did not believes and did not pray
  75,32,"but he said it was a lie, and turned his back"
  75,33,Then he went to his people haughtily
  75,34,"woe to thee, and woe to thee"
  75,35,"again woe to thee, and woe to thee"
  75,36,Does man think that he shall be left to himself
  75,37,Wasn't he a clot of emitted seed
  75,38,"Then he was congealed blood, and (God) created him, and fashioned him"
  75,39,"and made of him pairs, male and female"
  75,40,Is not He able to quicken the dead
  76,1,Does there not come on man a portion of time when he is nothing worth mentioning
  76,2,"Verily, We created man from a mingled clot, to try him; and we gave him hearing and sight"
  76,3,"Verily, we guided him in the way, whether he be grateful or ungrateful"
  76,4,"Verily, we have prepared for those who misbelieve chains and fetters and a blaze"
  76,5,"Verily, the righteous shall drink of a cup tempered with Kafur"
  76,6,a spring from which God's servants shall drink and make it gush out as they please
  76,7,"They who fulfill their vows, and fear a day, the evil which shall fly abroad"
  76,8,and who give food for His love to the poor and the orphan and the captive
  76,9,We only feed you for God's sake; we desire not from you either reward or thanks
  76,10,"we fear from our Lord a frowning, calamitous day"
  76,11,And God will guard them from the evil of that day and will cast on them brightness and joy
  76,12,and their reward for their patience shall be Paradise and silk
  76,13,reclining therein upon couches they shall neither see therein sun nor piercing cold
  76,14,and close down upon them shall be its shadows; and lowered over them its fruits to cull
  76,15,and they shall be served round with vessels of silver and goblets that are as flagons
  76,16,flagons of silver which they shall mete out
  76,17,and they shall drink therein a cup tempered with Zingabil
  76,18,a spring therein named Silsabil
  76,19,and there shall go round about them eternal boys; when thou seest them thou wilt think them scattered pearls
  76,20,and when thou seest them thou shalt see pleasure and a great estate
  76,21,On them shall be garments of green embroidered satin and brocade; and they shall be adorned with bracelets of silver; and their Lord shall give them to drink pure drink
  76,22,"Verily, this is a reward for you, and your efforts are thanked"
  76,23,"Verily, we have sent down upon thee the Qur'an"
  76,24,"Wherefore wait patiently for the judgment of thy Lord, and obey not any sinner or misbeliever amongst them"
  76,25,"But remember the name of thy Lord morning, and evening"
  76,26,"and through the night, and adore Him, and celebrate His praises the whole night long"
  76,27,"Verily, these love the transitory life, and leave behind them a heavy day"
  76,28,We created them and strengthened their joints; and if we please we can exchange for the likes of them in their stead
  76,29,"Verily, this is a memorial, and whoso will, let him take unto his Lord a way"
  76,30,"But ye will not please except God please! Verily, God is knowing, wise"
  76,31,He makes whomsoever He pleases to enter into His mercy; but the unjust He has prepared for them a grievous woe
  77,1,By those sent in a series
  77,2,And by those who speed swiftly
  77,3,And by the dispensers abroad
  77,4,And by the separators apart
  77,5,And by those who instil the reminder
  77,6,as an excuse or warning
  77,7,"Verily, what ye are threatened with shall surely happen"
  77,8,And when the stars shall be erased
  77,9,And when the heaven shall be cleft
  77,10,And when the mountains shall be winnowed
  77,11,And when the apostles shall have a time appointed for them
  77,12,For what day is the appointment made
  77,13,For the day of decision
  77,14,and what shall make thee know what the decision is
  77,15,Woe on that day for those who say it is a lie
  77,16,Have we not destroyed those of yore
  77,17,and then followed them up with those of the latter day
  77,18,Thus do we with the sinners
  77,19,Woe on that day for those who say it is a lie
  77,20,Did we not create you from contemptible water
  77,21,and place it in a sure depository
  77,22,unto a certain decreed term
  77,23,for we are able and well able too
  77,24,Woe on that day for those who say it is a lie
  77,25,Have we not made for them the earth
  77,26,to hold the living and the dead
  77,27,and set thereon firm mountains reared aloft? and given you to drink water in streams
  77,28,Woe on that day for those who say it is a lie
  77,29,Go off to that which ye did call a lie
  77,30,Go off to the shadow of three columns
  77,31,that shall not shade nor avail against the flame
  77,32,"Verily, it throws off sparks like towers"
  77,33,as though they were yellow camels
  77,34,Woe on that day for those who say it is a lie
  77,35,This is the day when they may not speak
  77,36,when they are not permitted to excuse themselves
  77,37,Woe on that day for those who say it is a lie
  77,38,This is the day of decision! We have assembled you with those of yore
  77,39,if ye have any stratagem employ it now
  77,40,Woe on that day for those who say it is a lie
  77,41,"Verily, the pious are amid shades and springs"
  77,42,and fruit such as they love
  77,43,"Eat and drink with good digestion, for that which ye have done"
  77,44,"Verily, thus do we reward those who do well"
  77,45,Woe on that day for those who say it is a lie
  77,46,"Eat and enjoy yourselves for a little; verily, ye are sinners"
  77,47,Woe on that day for those who say it is a lie
  77,48,"And when it is said to them bow down, they bow not down"
  77,49,Woe on that day for those who say it is a lie
  77,50,And in what new discourse after it will they believe